HEADWORD: Windpipe
<hw>Wind"pipe`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Anat.)</fld>
<def>The passage for the breath from the larynx to the lungs; the
trachea; the weasand. See <xex>Illust.</xex> under
<er>Lung</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

